<Base title="What Happened to Moxie? — Nolte" description="In 2023, Moxie became Nolte. Same founder, same commitment to quality — evolved into a consultative product partner for regulated industries.">

  <header class="hero">
    <span class="eyebrow">Our Story</span>
    <h1>What happened to <em>Moxie?</em></h1>
  </header>

  <div class="prose legal-prose">

    <p>In fall 2023, Moxie became <strong>Nolte</strong>.</p>

    <p>The name changed because the company changed. What started as a digital product studio in SoHo nearly two decades ago evolved into something more specific and more opinionated — a consultative product partner for regulated industries, where the stakes are real and the margin for error is thin.</p>

    <p>The rebrand reflected a commitment Jeffrey Nolte had been building toward for years: put your name on the work and own the outcomes. Not as a branding exercise, but as an operating principle. If the delivery doesn't ship, you don't pay. That kind of guarantee only works when you stand behind it personally.</p>

    <h2>What stayed the same</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The same founder, Jeffrey Nolte, leading the company since 2006</li>
      <li>The same commitment to quality and accountability</li>
      <li>The same team — now spanning multiple countries and time zones</li>
      <li>The same clients, many of whom have been with us for years</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What changed</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Positioning:</strong> From a general product studio to a consultative product partner for regulated industries (insurance, healthcare, finance)</li>
      <li><strong>Methodology:</strong> NolteOS — a predictive delivery system built on 20 years of data, replacing estimation with forecasting</li>
      <li><strong>Pricing:</strong> Fixed price per delivery, not hourly billing</li>
      <li><strong>Guarantee:</strong> If it doesn't ship, you don't pay</li>
    </ul>

    <p>If you were a Moxie client, nothing changed about your engagement. If you're new here — <a href="/contact">let's talk</a>.</p>

  </div>

</Base>

